-- 
China to Improve Emergency Nuclear Steps, Daily Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-09T01:56:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/china-to-improve-emergency-nuclear-steps-daily-says-correct-.html
(Corrects date of earthquake.)  China will improve emergency
procedures at its nuclear  power plants  to deal with disasters
like what happened after the March 11 earthquake and tsunami in
Japan,  China Daily  reported, citing Liu Hua, head of the nuclear
safety and radioactive safety management department under the
Ministry of Environmental Protection.  The government may work with State Grid Corp. to develop
plans to guarantee power supply to nuclear power plants in
crisis to prevent a possible shutdown of a reactor’s cooling
system like what befell Japan’s Fukushima Dai-Ichi station, Liu
said, according to the newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gregory Turk at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  